				<TR><TD ALIGN="right" VALIGN="top"><SPAN CLASS="text"><B>Event Title: </B></SPAN></TD><TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><SPAN CLASS="text">Chardock Raid - Cleric Epic</SPAN></TD></TR>
			
				<TR><TD ALIGN="right" VALIGN="top"><SPAN CLASS="text"><B>Time (please state what time zone): </B></SPAN></TD><TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><SPAN CLASS="text"></SPAN></TD></TR>
			
				<TR><TD ALIGN="right" VALIGN="top"><SPAN CLASS="text"><B># of People Needed: </B></SPAN></TD><TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><SPAN CLASS="text">NATO Raid - Sanabien Healgood</SPAN></TD></TR>
			
				<TR><TD ALIGN="right" VALIGN="top"><SPAN CLASS="text"><B>Description: </B></SPAN></TD><TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><SPAN CLASS="text">Date: Friday, April 18th
Time: 6pm Pacific Standard Time (8pm CST - 9pm EST)
Gather Time: One hour prior to raid 5pm PST
Zone: Chardock
Mob: Overking Bathezid
Level: 65 with 32k hitpoints
Hosting Guild: Jemand Verbieten
Epic Piece for: Sanabien Healgood

Tactic:
Everybody says he is a wuss, but he has a LOT of guards and getting to him can be tricky.  A high level enchanter and rogue can use bind sight and pacify just about every mob down to Overking Bathezid, so your raid force doesn't even have to fight many battles.  Using this same trick, you can supposedly pacify the whole room where Overking Bathezid is located, and then you can single pull him in to the hall and kick his butt.
 
There are cleric, enchanter, necro, and warrior epic drops in Chardok, and all four of the mobs King, Queen, Prince, and Herbalist are all in the same general area.  That means that if we have a *LARGE* enough raid force, we *MIGHT* be able to get an epic hit or two for each of these classes on the same raid.  I am told that the Overking Bathezid spawns on a 1 hour interval, so it is possible that we can get multiple cleric epic hits in on one raid.
 
A 65 shaman, 65 Enchanter, and 60 Warrior will be coming to help.  That being said, I would greatly appreciate it if I could get a large following of NATO members on board for this one.  I am certain that I am making this hit out to be worse then it really is, but something just keeps telling me to play it safe. 

   </SPAN></TD></TR>
			
